quran[16]{c,v,t,f}:
  55,58,"As if they were rubies and coral.{1}",1:[In purity, color and beauty.]
  55,59,"So which of the favors of your Lord would you deny?"
  55,60,"Is the reward for good [anything] but good?"
  56,49,"Say, [O Muḥammad], "
  56,50,"Are to be gathered together for the appointment of a known Day."
  56,51,"Then indeed you, O those astray [who are] deniers,"
  61,13,"And [you will obtain] another [favor] that you love - victory from Allāh and an imminent conquest; and give good tidings to the believers."
  61,14,"O you who have believed, be supporters of Allāh, as when Jesus, the son of Mary, said to the disciples, "
  62,10,"And when the prayer has been concluded, disperse within the land and seek from the bounty of Allāh, and remember Allāh often that you may succeed."
  62,11,"But [on one occasion] when they saw a transaction or a diversion, [O Muḥammad], they rushed to it and left you standing. Say, "
  63,7,"They are the ones who say, "
  63,8,"They say, "
  63,9,"O you who have believed, let not your wealth and your children divert you from the remembrance of Allāh. And whoever does that - then those are the losers."
  64,1,"Whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth is exalting Allāh.{1} To Him belongs dominion, and to Him belongs [all] praise, and He is over all things competent.",1:[See footnote to 57:1.]
  64,2,"It is He who created you, and among you is the disbeliever, and among you is the believer. And Allāh, of what you do, is Seeing."
  64,3,"He created the heavens and earth in truth and formed you and perfected your forms; and to Him is the [final] destination."